\par\plain \f1\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 INVINCIBLE DREAD is the first part of a three-part novel of epic fantasy. It is complete at 130,000 words. It combines the brutal desert styling of Cormac McCarthy\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8217\'92s BLOOD MERIDIAN, with the drug-addled odyssey of Hunter S. Thompson\u8217\'92s FEAR AND LOATHING IN LAS VEGAS, all wrapped up in a spiritually charged fantasy world inspired by ancient Mesopotamia. It follows a disillusioned painter who has fallen in with a troupe of desert bandits who aim to free a god from captivity.}
\par\plain \f1\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 By the age of ten, Mandrameen could paint a portrait in oils that rivaled the old Jeketian masters. By the age of twenty, he was wasting away on a barren farm while getting high on burgeons. A black robed witch visits his farm. She tells of an ancient prophecy, and she believes Mandrameen may play a part\hich\f1 \emdash \loch\f1 but he\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8217\'92s not meant to save the world, he\u8217\'92s meant to destroy it.}
\par\plain \f1\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Mandrameen undergoes a test\hich\f1 \emdash \loch\f1 he must paint a portrait using only shades of black. The dark face he paints comes alive and emerges from the canvas, but Mandrameen, frightened, gives it a hearty kick. Having just upset a ritual to summon the god of all destruction, Mandrameen is killed.}
\par\plain \f1\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 His body is found by a band of no-ordinary bandits, for among them is a much friendlier witch who brings him back to life. These bandits are led by the manliest of all possible men, Ayram, and they call themselves the Ayramun. Ayram\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8217\'92s goal is to strike a blow at the oppressive Hrkan Lords by freeing the god of all creation.}
\par\plain \f1\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Together they struggle through a desert that is squeezed dry by Hrkan might. Cannibalistic tribes lurk in desert temples. Demons are hiding in the ground. Worse, everyone Mandrameen meets wants to tell him who he is, and what he\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8217\'92s meant for. In the end, he must decide between a budding friendship, incredible sacrifice, and the divine purpose written down for him when the world was made.}
